<p>I want to add an empty header in my HTTP packet; something like:</p>  <pre><code>Someheader: </code></pre>  <p>But I see in an old topics that libcurl does not support that. They propose a workaround by concatenating the empty header with another header:</p>  <pre><code>"Someheader:\r\nheader1: value" </code></pre>  <p>Does the latest libcurl offer another, more proper, way to send an empty header?</p>